Cleaning Data¶

In [953]:
def filling_test(mean:float,median:float,mode:float,col_name:str)->tuple:
    # fig, ax =plt.subplots(1,3)
    test1 = house[col_name].fillna(mean)
    test2 = house[col_name].fillna(median)
    test3 = house[col_name].fillna(mode)
    fill = house[col_name].dropna()
    test4 = house[col_name].fillna(pd.Series(np.random.choice(fill , size = len(house.index))))
    
    sns.displot([test1.values,house[col_name].values],rug=True,kind='kde',legend=False,palette='magma')
    plt.title('test1')
    sns.displot([test2.values,house[col_name].values],rug=True,kind='kde',legend=False,palette='magma')
    plt.title('test2')
    sns.displot([test3.values,house[col_name].values],rug=True,kind='kde',legend=False,palette='magma')
    plt.title('test3')
    sns.displot([test4.values,house[col_name].values],rug=True,kind='kde',legend=False,palette='magma')
    plt.title('test4')
    return test1,test2,test3,test4

def plot_two_distribution(data1,data2):
    data1.value_counts().plot(kind='kde',alpha=0.5)
    data2.value_counts().plot(kind='kde',alpha=0.9)
    plt.legend(['before','after'])

def random_selection_filling_missing_values(column_name):
    fill = house[column_name].dropna()
    test = house[column_name].fillna(pd.Series(np.random.choice(fill , size = len(house.index))))
    return test

def filling_missing_values(mean,median,mode,column_name:str):
    filling_by_mean = house[column_name].fillna(mean)
    filling_by_median = house[column_name].fillna(median)
    filling_by_mode = house[column_name].fillna(mode)
    return filling_by_mean,filling_by_median,filling_by_mode

def normalize (col_name):
    min_ = house[col_name].min()
    max_ = house[col_name].max()
    house[col_name] = (house[col_name] - min_)/(max_-min_)
